article.headline: Columbia wins 84-81 against Pennsylvania
article.description: — Geronimo Rubio De La Rosa scored 24 points as Columbia beat Pennsylvania 84-81 on Saturday.

article.story: NEW YORK -- — Geronimo Rubio De La Rosa scored 24 points as Columbia beat Pennsylvania 84-81 on Saturday. De La Rosa was 6 of 11 shooting, including 5 for 9 from 3-point range, and went 7 for 8 from the line for the Lions (10-7, 1/3 Ivy League). Kenny Noland added 15 points while going 6 of 8 (3 for 4 from 3-point range), and also had five rebounds. Zavian McLean had 12 points and went 5 of 6 from the field. Tyler Perkins led the Quakers (9-10, 1-3) in scoring, finishing with 25 points and eight rebounds. Nick Spinoso added 17 points, eight rebounds and two steals for Pennsylvania. In addition, Eddie Holland III had 15 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
